THIRD-PARTY COMPONENTS

This skill is a set of Markdown guides and small Python CLI wrappers. It does
NOT bundle or redistribute the following libraries; it merely invokes them at
runtime. Their own licenses apply to their own code:

- pypdf ............... BSD-3-Clause (https://github.com/py-pdf/pypdf)
- pdfplumber .......... MIT          (https://github.com/jsvine/pdfplumber)
- pypdfium2 ........... Apache-2.0 or BSD-3-Clause (dual)
                        wraps PDFium (BSD-3-Clause) — Chromium's PDF engine
- reportlab (open) .... BSD-3-Clause (https://www.reportlab.com/)
- pdf-lib (JS) ........ MIT          (https://github.com/Hopding/pdf-lib)
- pdfjs-dist (JS) ..... Apache-2.0   (Mozilla PDF.js)
- pypng / Pillow ...... MIT / PIL-style permissive
- pytesseract wrapper . Apache-2.0   (Tesseract itself is Apache-2.0)
- qpdf (CLI) .......... Apache-2.0
- poppler-utils (CLI) . GPL-2.0      — invoked only as an external command;
                        no source code is copied or linked. Redistributing the
                        poppler binaries is subject to GPL. If you cannot
                        accept GPL on external tooling, avoid `pdftotext`,
                        `pdftoppm`, and `pdfimages`; the Python-only path in
                        this skill (pypdf + pypdfium2 + pdfplumber + reportlab)
                        is fully permissive.
- ImageMagick (CLI) ... ImageMagick License (Apache-2.0 style) — optional,
                        used only in the forms zoom-refinement flow.

This skill is an independent implementation. The recipes below are written
from scratch against the linked libraries' public documentation.
